==English==

===Pronunciation===
like "etch" (except with a "bl" in front)

===Interjection===
'''blech'''
#An imitation of the sound of [[gag]]ging, used to express disgust or disdain.
#:''Blech! Look at all the garbage people add to the online dictionary! 

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|blech||}}
# To have the vomiting reflex triggered.  A very technical term used to express disfavor towards something posted by a fellow subscriber, and often appears in mailing list forums, such as the Progress Email Group (www.peg.com).

===Alternative spellings===
*'''Blecccchhh!'''
*'''Blecccccccchhhhhhhhh!!!'''
* Any repeating series of c, h, and !, in sequence, is allowed. Repeating the e is not acceptable, because then it might sound like bleach. And while bleach would certainly cause vomiting, that is something altogether different.]

